EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to taxation; requiring the Department of Taxation
to develop and operate with financial institutions a system
for matching data for the collection of certain debts owed
to the State; authorizing the Department to disclose
certain confidential information to certain financial
institutions for certain purposes; revising certain
provisions relating to certain information held by
financial institutions; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Department of Taxation, which has various powers and
2 duties related to the administration and collection of certain taxes, fees, assessments
3 and other amounts of money. (Chapter 360 of NRS) If a person owes delinquent
4 taxes or has a deficiency determination against him or her with respect to any tax
5 administered by the Department, existing law authorizes the Department to attempt
6 collection of the tax or deficiency in certain ways. (NRS 360.4193, 360.420,
7 360.473, 360.483) Section 1 of this bill requires the Department to develop and
8 operate a system for matching data to collect certain outstanding debts owed to the
9 State. Pursuant to section 1, financial institutions in this State must: (1) provide to
10 the Department information on persons who maintain accounts at the financial
11 institution and are identified by the Department as owing outstanding debts to the
12 State; and (2) encumber certain assets held in the financial institution by the debtors
13 to pay their debts.
14 Existing law makes the records and files of the Department of Taxation
15 concerning the administration and collection of taxes, fees, assessments and other
16 amounts and the imposition of disciplinary action confidential and privileged, but
-
