– 2 –
17 authorizes the disclosure of such records and files under certain circumstances.
18 (NRS 360.255) Section 2 of this bill provides that the Department may disclose
19 certain confidential information to certain financial institutions for the purpose of
20 carrying out the provisions of section 1.
21 Existing law prohibits, with certain exceptions, a governmental agency from
22 requesting, and a financial institution from providing, certain financial records of
23 certain customers. (NRS 239A.070, 239A.080) Section 3 of this bill provides that
24 the Department may request, and a financial institution may provide to the
25 Department in response to such a request, certain financial records of certain
26 customers of the financial institution who owe outstanding debts to the State.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 360 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Department shall enter into agreements with financial
4 institutions doing business in this State to coordinate the
5 development and operation of a system for matching data, using
6 automated exchanges of data to the maximum extent feasible.
7 2. In addition to any other remedy provided for in this
8 chapter, the Department may use the system for matching data
9 developed and operated pursuant to subsection 1 to collect a debt,
10 plus any applicable penalties and interest.
11 3. A financial institution in this State shall:
12 (a) Cooperate with the Department in carrying out the
13 provisions of subsection 1.
14 (b) Use the system to provide to the Department for each
15 calendar quarter the name, address of record, social security
16 number or other number assigned for taxpayer identification of
17 each person who maintains an account at the financial institution,
18 as identified by the Department by name and social security
19 number or other number assigned for taxpayer identification.
20 (c) In response to the receipt from the Department of
21 notification of debt that a person owes the State, encumber on
22 behalf of the Department a portion of the assets of the person held
23 by the financial institution sufficient to cover the debt and
24 surrender those assets to the Department. A financial institution is
25 not required to encumber or surrender any assets received by the
26 financial institution on behalf of the person after the financial
27 institution received the notice of the debt from the Department.
28 4. A financial institution may not be held liable in any civil or
29 criminal action for:
30 (a) Any disclosure of information to the Department pursuant
31 to this section.
